    <title id="1">Adding and Maintaining Routes for a VXLAN Network</title>
    <shortdesc id="2">You can add or delete routing table entries for hosts on a VXLAN
        network using the CLI.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author id="3">Jim Owens</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <prereq id="prereq_N1001F_N1001C_N10001" id="4">
            <p id="5">The compute node must be locked.</p>
        </prereq>
        <context id="context_N1002D_N1001F_N10001" id="68">
            <p id="69">To add routes, use the following command.</p>
            <codeblock id="70"><systemoutput id="73">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput id="76">system host-route-add <varname id="79">node</varname> <varname id="81">ifname</varname> <varname id="83">network</varname> <varname id="85">prefix</varname> <varname id="86">gateway</varname> <varname id="87">metric</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <p id="51">where</p>
            <parml>
                <plentry id="52">
                    <pt id="53">node</pt>
                    <pd id="54">
                        <p id="55">is the name or UUID of the compute node</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry id="56">
                    <pt id="57">ifname</pt>
                    <pd id="58">
                        <p id="59">is the name of the interface</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry id="60">
                    <pt id="61">network</pt>
                    <pd id="62">
                        <p id="63">is an IPv4 or IPv6 network address</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry id="91">
                    <pt id="94">prefix</pt>
                    <pd id="97">
                        <p id="100">is the netmask length for the network address</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry id="92">
                    <pt id="95">gateway</pt>
                    <pd id="98">
                        <p id="101">is the default gateway</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry id="93">
                    <pt id="96">metric</pt>
                    <pd id="99">
                        <p id="102">is the cost of the route (the number of hops)</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
            </parml>
            <p id="103">To delete routes, use the following command.</p>
            <codeblock id="71"><systemoutput id="74">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput id="77">system host-route-delete <varname id="80">uuid</varname> <varname id="82">ifname</varname> <varname id="84">network</varname> <varname id="88">prefix</varname> <varname id="89">gateway</varname> <varname id="90">metric</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <p id="104">where <nameliteral id="105">uuid</nameliteral> is the UUID of the route to be deleted.</p>
            <p id="106">To list existing routes, including their UUIDs, use the following command.</p>
            <codeblock id="72"><systemoutput id="75">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput id="78">system host-route-list compute-0</userinput></codeblock>
        </context>
    </taskbody>
</task-wr>